org.grouplens.grapht.reflect

Interface InjectionPoint

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstructorParameterInjectionPoint, FieldInjectionPoint, NoArgumentInjectionPoint, SetterInjectionPoint, SimpleInjectionPoint

    public interface InjectionPoint
extends Serializable
    InjectionPoint represents a point of injection for an instantiable type. Examples include a constructor parameter, a setter method, or a field.
    Author:
    GroupLens Research

      • getQualifier

        @Nullable
Annotation getQualifier()
        Return the qualifier annotation added to the injection point. The returned annotation's type will have been annotated with Qualifier. If the injection point is not qualified, this will return null.
        Returns:
        Any qualifier applied to the injection point

      • getAttribute

        @Nullable
<A extends Annotation> A getAttribute(Class<A> atype)
        Return the attribute of type A that is applied to the injection point. If the injection point does not have an attribute of type A, then null is returned.
        Parameters:
        atype - Attribute annotation type. It must be annotated with Attribute.
        Returns:
        The instance of A applied to the injection point, or null
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if atype is null

      • getAttributes

        @Nonnull
Collection<Annotation> getAttributes()
        Returns:
        Immutable collection of attribute annotations (does not include the qualifier)

      • getMember

        @Nullable
Member getMember()
        Return the Member that produced this injection point. Synthetic injection points can have a null member.
        Returns:
        The Member that produces this injection point

      • isNullable

        boolean isNullable()
        Returns:
        True if this injection point accepts null values
